        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Redesign Control UI channels directory",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\r\n\r\nThe Control UI Channels page was hard to scan because every channel rendered as a full card and the raw status snapshot was always visible. That made it harder to quickly tell which channels are enabled, disabled, or need attention.\r\n\r\n## Why This Change Was Made\r\n\r\nThis redesign turns Channels into a filterable directory with compact rows, channel logos, status dots, and expandable details. The detailed status/config content still exists, but it now lives inside each expanded row, while the raw Gateway snapshot is tucked behind a disclosure.\r\n\r\nIt also keeps expanded channel rows in the URL query string so a focused channel view can survive reloads or be shared.\r\n\r\n## User Impact\r\n\r\nUsers can scan channel status faster, filter by enabled or disabled channels, expand only the channel they are working on, and still access the existing per-channel configuration controls. Collapsed rows also surface summary and account-level errors through the warning status dot.\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n\r\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/channels.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-channels.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/channels.test.ts ui/src/ui/navigation.test.ts`\r\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:ui`\r\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:check`\r\n- `pnpm ui:build` passed with the existing large chunk warning\r\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` clean: no accepted/actionable findings\r\n\r\nImages:\r\nBefore :\r\n<img width=\"1483\" height=\"841\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/11222114-d5cb-47e7-b923-40a1e8da1494\" />\r\n\r\nAfter\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1072\" height=\"846\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-23 at 1 00 37 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/762699b4-a9ce-4ea1-a577-55ad3b8a18cd\" />\r\n\r\n\r\nFull `pnpm check && pnpm test` was not run; validation was targeted to the Control UI channels surface.\r\n\r\nHuman + AI assisted PR.\r\n",
        "branch": "ui/channels-directory-redesign",
